<section style="position:relative;height:360px;display:flex;align-items:flex-end;">
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background-image:url('/uploads/Hancock-plastering-and-painting%20(4).webp');background-size:cover;background-position:center 40%;"></div>
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background:linear-gradient(to top,rgba(15,23,42,0.92) 0%,rgba(15,23,42,0.5) 55%,rgba(15,23,42,0.18) 100%);"></div>
  <div style="position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 48px;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin:0 0 12px;"><a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Home</a> / <a href="/areas" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Areas</a> / Gerrards Cross</p>
    <h1 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(30px,5vw,52px);font-weight:700;color:#ffffff;margin:0 0 10px;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:1.05;">Plasterer in Gerrards Cross</h1>
    <p style="font-size:16px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);margin:0;">SL9 · High-end plastering &amp; decorating for Gerrards Cross and Chalfont St Peter.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">About Gerrards Cross</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">One of the most affluent residential areas in the service corridor. Large detached properties and executive homes, often with high-specification interior finish expectations.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Gerrards Cross is consistently ranked among the most expensive residential areas outside Central London. The housing stock is predominantly large detached — 1920s–50s executive properties alongside more recent high-value developments. Homeowners here expect a high standard and a professional approach.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Venetian plastering enquiries are a consistent feature from Gerrards Cross — polished plaster in hallways, master bedrooms, and feature walls is a natural fit for the interior standards in this postcode. Sash window painting is relevant on the older properties. Exterior render maintenance on the rendered stock.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#F8FAFC;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Common problems</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 28px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;">What goes wrong in Gerrards Cross's housing stock.</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Large render elevations</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">The big executive houses present substantial rendered elevations that weather and craze, needing patch repair and a premium masonry paint system applied properly.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">High-spec interior wear</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Where polished plaster and high-end finishes already exist, repair and re-application has to match the original exactly — there's no hiding a patch in a Venetian wall.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Sash window upkeep</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">The older properties have original sash windows that need periodic strip, repair and repainting to keep water out and the timber sound.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
