        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Gerrards Cross is consistently among the most expensive residential areas outside Central London. The housing is predominantly large detached — 1920s–50s executive properties around the town and station, alongside more recent high-value developments, extending into <strong>Chalfont St Peter</strong>. Homeowners here expect a high standard and a professional, discreet approach.</p>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">It's a postcode where the finish is expected to match the address — and where polished plaster fits naturally into the interior standards.</p>
      </div>
